caption:
A recap on yesterday’s FRAME Designathon 🖼️🤩✨

Thank you so much to everyone who showed up, and our judges and mentors for supporting the event! All teams made amazing work and we were blown away by your creative talent and ideas :)

Congrats again to the top 3 teams: 
Evening Brew, Stamped, and LaLeada! 🎊

Special thank you to @sweetlouscookies @dominoswaterloo for providing us the delicious food at our event, and to the Student Life Endowment Fund for their support! We couldn’t have done it without you 💙

We hope that you were able to grow your design thinking skills and implementation. Take this as an opportunity to add a new case study to your portfolio! ☺️ 

✨ Stay tuned for more design challenges like this in the future!

***

#uwaterloo #ux #uxdesignlife #designathon #design #figma #figmadesign

Meet the judges and our mentors for tomorrow’s FRAME Designathon! 🤩

Less than 24 hours before our designathon starts tomorrow! 😱 We wanted to take a moment to spotlight out an incredible lineup of talented judges and mentors experienced in UX/UI and Product Design, along with our sponsors!

Meet your judges: Aileen Luo, Yinan Zhang, and Yousuf Zia! They will be evaluating your projects and selecting the winners based on creativity, implementation, user-centred design, and more!

Our awesome mentors will be there to guide you throughout the designathon to offer you advice, share their expertise + helpful resources, and answer any questions you might have 🔎

We’d also love to give a huge thank you to our sponsors @sweetlouscookies, @dominoswaterloo, and the Student Life Endowment Fund for their wonderful support and making this event possible 💙🍪✨

We can’t wait to see you there! Best of luck to those who are participating 🙂‍↕️✨

caption:
In May, WUSA received a member-submitted petition requesting a referendum. After deliberation by the Elections and Referenda Committee (ERC), the ERC recommended questions to Board, who approved the recommended questions. The referendum process will officially begin shortly! 
 
The approved referendum questions relate to the University of Waterloo’s partnership with Technion and ensuring responsible partnerships and investments. Please click the link in our bio to read the full announcement and for more information.

caption: Curious about how decisions are made on campus? Let’s break down the process of a referendum from start to finish. Swipe through to learn how an idea becomes a campus-wide decision. Your vote matters, so stay informed and get involved!

caption:
Thinking about joining the Board but you aren’t sure what it looks like? 🤔 We’re here to walk you through what the first few months of being on the WUSA Board of Directors looks like! 

First things first- our Board goes on a retreat 🏝️This is where they learn some of the skills they will need to help advocate for their stakeholders (aka you🫵). Some topics covered at this year’s retreat include job responsibilities, budgeting, and an overview of WUSA services. 

After this retreat, all the board members participated in media training 📸 While Nick and Arya are the primary spokespeople for WUSA, all members are trained on how to best communicate with students and others on socials. 

During this time there have also been 3 monthly Board meetings. To watch the full meetings, head to our YouTube or check out the articles at wusa.ca. For a quick recap, check out our Reels page for ‘what you missed at the Board meeting in under 60 seconds”. 

Going forward, the Board will focus on the annual plan and the budget for the 2024-2025 year. After that, they will tackle the 5-year plan for 2025-2030, which will set the organization’s direction for the next 5 years. 

#leadership #wusa #WUSAboard #studentleadership

caption: We in fact distracted everyone in the office to film this video🤭🫣

We hit the halls to see if students could guess some of the Representative Survey Platform results  📊
 
The RSP Platform is a program where a representative population of undergrads are asked to fill out surveys that relate to student issues, twice a year. WUSA then uses this information to ensure that our services and decisions align with our undergrads’ best interests. For the full details check out the 🔗 in our bio!
